<section xml:id="Section_8_3">
        <title>Section 8.3</title>
<subsection xml:id="Problem_8_3_2">
     <title>Problem 1</title>
</subsection>
<ol marker="(a)">
    <li>
        <p>
            Let <m>r</m> be a primitive root modulo <m>p^n.</m> 
            Let
            <md>
                k=\text{ord}_p r.
            </md>
            Then 
            <md>
            r^k \equiv 1 \pmod{p}.   
            </md>
            We have <m>p-1|k.</m>
            We can also write: 
            <md>
                p|r^k-1
            </md>
            or 
            <md>
                ps+1=r^k
            </md>
            for some integer <m>s.</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            Per the hint: Show 
            <md>
                r^{pk} \equiv 1 \pmod{p^2}.
            </md>
            
        
            
        </p>
    </li>
</ol>
    
</section>